Admission: Through Entrance Test

On the basis of merit through an RPVT competitive entrance examination conducted byÂ Rajasthan University of Veterinary &amp; Animal Science.
<h3>Minimum Eligibility Qualification</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">10+2 examination/equivalent examination conducted by an Education Board/University/Council (duly recognized by the Rajasthan Board, CBSE, New Delhi) with not less than pass marks in each subject and not less than 50% marks in the aggregate of English, Physics, Chemistry and Biology. However, in the case of SC/ST candidates, the minimum aggregate required is 40%. OR Any examination of a University/Education Board/ College/School in a foreign country recognized by the Academic Council as an equivalent for the purpose with good knowledge of English.</p>

<h3>Minimum Age</h3>
17 years on or before the 31 December of the year of his/her admission to the 1st year of B.V.Sc. &amp; A.H. course.
<h3>Allocation of seats</h3>
1. 85% of sanctioned seats are reserved for Rajasthan domicile candidates.
2. Only 15% of seats are opened for All India Competitive Examination.
3. Regular seats: 28 at Bikaner, 40 at Navania, (Udaipur) and 40 at Jaipur.
4. Payment seats: 40 at Bikaner, 40Â at Navania, (Udaipur) and 40 at PGIVR Jaipur. (Payment seat fees: Rs 2.00 lac
in addition to the regular fee per year)
